
[1]industriously

   INDUS'TRIOUSLY, adv. With habitual diligence; with steady application
   of the powers of body or of mind.

   1. Diligently; assiduously; with care; applied to a particular purpose.
   He attempted industriously to make peace. He industriously concealed
   his name.
